properties.Creator: Baranoucky, Ruth
properties.Description:
Lithuanian
Performers, Lithuanian Group [from the Church of the Immaculate Conception]
This song is used throughout the year, especially during May and October, the months of the Virgin Mary.
        "Maria, you are like a pure lily,
        You shine high in heaven;
        Ease our burdens,
        Help us people,
        Help from our enemies.
        We sinners beg of your mercy.
        Those who fall by the wayside,
        Give them strength and lead them
        Between sighing oceans -
        These earthly wars -
        Those fallen, help them."
        [Also AFS 8468 B1, PM 51 /7]

properties.Creator: Stacy, Stella
properties.Description:
Peyote religious song
The rapid beat and chant typical of peyote music. The chant is repeated four times.
"He is the only hope that I have, the Holy Son of God."

Blow Snake's nephew brought this thought back, and Blow Snake put it into a song which will be perpetuated. It is in honor of a GI boy from the last war, and is sung by his uncle Blow Snake and the women folks.
Thought: The hardships that the young man endured were appreciated by his uncle Blow Snake, who wrote the song.
